main event: A green object with an orange tail was observed in Omaha, Nebraska, following an erratic course for approximately 9 to 11 seconds.
interesting points: The object was described as oval-shaped and fluorescent light green., The tail of the object trailed a flame that transitioned from bright red-orange to yellow., The sighting occurred while traveling in a car, viewed through the windshield., It was noted that there was no air traffic at the time of the sighting., Local astronomers had no record of such a meteor on the date of the sighting.
sighted object: green oval object with an orange tail
witness description: Two civilians, one described as a student from Lincoln, Nebraska, and the other as a major in the USAF.
